cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a reinforcement learning-based closed loop power control algorithm for the downlink of the voice over LTE (VoLTE) radio bearer for an indoor environment served by small cells. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a Q-learning algorithm for VoLTE closed loop power control. This falls under the domain of machine learning.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a reinforcement learning-based algorithm for performance tuning problems in an indoor cellular network. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the effective signal to interference plus noise ratio due to neighboring cell failure, which is an important parameter in information theory.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a closed loop power control algorithm for VoLTE in an indoor environment served by small cells. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
